[[Image:NACCL20 cropped.JPG|right|thumb|Logo from NACCL-20, held in 2008]] The '''North American Conference on Chinese Linguistics''' (NACCL) is an annual [[academic conference]] that focuses on research in [[Chinese language]] and [[linguistics]].
The conference was first held in 1989 at [[Ohio State University]], as the Northeast Conference on Chinese Linguistics (NECCL), and changed its name to "North American Conference on Chinese Linguistics" at its third annual session in 1991.<ref name="chan">{{cite web | title=History of NACCL: The First Two Decades | url=http://chinalinks.osu.edu/naccl-20/proceedings/NACCL_history.pdf | last=Chan | first=Marjorie K.M. | publisher=[[Ohio State University]] | work=Proceedings of the 20th North American Conference on Chinese Linguistics (NACCL-20) | year=2008 | accessdate=2008-10-21}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.usc.edu/schools/college/ealc//chinling/naccl2.htm | title=Chinese Linguistics: NACCL | publisher=[[University of Southern California]] | accessdate=2008-10-21}}</ref> It is held every year in late spring, and includes both theoretical and empirical research from all subfields of Chinese linguistics;<ref name="chan"/> presenters include graduate students in addition to professors and other well-established scholars. The conference generally hosts talks both in Chinese and in English. The proceedings are published annually after the conference is finished; after NACCL-20 in 2008, the proceedings were published online for the first time.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://chinalinks.osu.edu/naccl-20/proceedings/preface.pdf | title=Preface | work=Proceedings of the 20th North American Conference on Chinese Linguistics (NACCL-20) | year=2008 | accessdate=2008-10-21 | last=Chan | first=Marjorie K.M.}}</ref>
Subjects presented include: Sociolinguistics, Phonetics/Phonology, Syntax, Semantics, Pragmatics, Orthography, Historical linguistics, Computational/Corpus Linguistics, Language Acquisition, Psycholinguistics, and Morphology.
